\par \tab \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 He did not die when he woke. Rather, Haelin found himself free. The girl continued to sing, her voice a bare whisper. She lay on Kel\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 l\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 
s chest. On the straw around them, Horst and his men slept. As the girl\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s voice died out, Kell\hich\f0 \rquote \loch\f0 s eyes opened. Haelin gestured him to silence. As he rose, Kell brought the girl up with him.
