\par \tab \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 Kell opened his mouth to speak. At that moment, Horst mumbled in his sleep and shifted. Kell frowned. He turned and, saying nothing more, left. Haelin watched him depart, then tur\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 
ned back to the sleeping four. They had no bows, no crossbows, only swords. Haelin sat down, positioning himself between them and the door, and he began to meditate, to draw what power he could.
\par \tab \hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 Horst was the first to rise. He looked around, then kicked h\hich\af0\dbch\af12\loch\f0 is men awake. He turned on Haelin.
